Tom Nosek game 1.
Tape missing intros, Jeopardy! Round, and 3 clues from Double Jeopardy! Round.

(1, 1).clue: This city's Seagram Building was designed by Ludwig Mies van der Rohe & Philip Johnson in the 1950s

(2, 1).clue: On December 24, 1871 this opera premiered in Cairo, Egypt

(3, 1).clue: This nation observes Mahatma Gandhi's birthday on October 2

(4, 1).clue: The 1st planting of this flower in Holland reportedly occurred at the University of Leiden in 1593

(5, 1).clue: After 17 years as Chief Justice, he stepped down in 1986

(6, 1).clue: In a William Blake poem, this animal was "burning bright in the forests of the night"

(1, 2).clue: In 1887 he designed his 1st building while working for Joseph Lyman Silsbee in Chicago

(2, 2).clue: To save her husband, Florestan, Leonore disguises herself as this young man in a Beethoven opera

(3, 2).clue: Philippine-American Friendship Day is observed on this day the U.S. celebrates its independence

(4, 2).clue: This flower was discovered in the mountains of Mexico in the 16th C. & named for botanist Andreas Dahl

(5, 2).clue: In January 1801 this Secretary of State was appointed Chief Justice by president John Adams

(6, 2).clue: "His poem "Starting from Paumanok" first appeared in "Leaves of Grass" under the title "Proto-Leaf"

(1, 3).clue: It's the more common name for tall casement windows, from the country where they were developed

(3, 3).clue: In Hong Kong, as in Great Britain, the day after Christmas is called this

(4, 3).clue: The Damask variety of this flower yields attar, an essential oil used in perfumes

(5, 3).clue: As Chief Justice, this ex-president was responsible for Congress' approval of a new Supreme Court building

(6, 3).clue: Rudyard Kipling wrote of being "On the road to" this city, "Where the flyin' fishes play"

(1, 4).clue: The Baroque style of architecture began in this European capital city in the early 1600s

(3, 4).clue: Celebrated in early fall, Choo Suk is the Thanksgiving of the southern part of this country

(4, 4).clue: Also called the yellow daisy, it's Maryland's state flower

(5, 4).clue: Before being named to the court in 1971, he served as an assistant Attorney General

(6, 4).clue: This poet lived most of his life with an unrequited love for Irish patriot Maude Gonne

(1, 5).clue: It's a support built against a Gothic structure's outer wall

(3, 5).clue: This founder of modern Turkey is memorialized on November 10

(4, 5).clue: It's the floral emblem of Japan's imperial family

(5, 5).clue: He wrote the opinion in the 1954 case Brown v. Board of Education of Topeka

(6, 5).clue: Robert Frost ended this poem with "Good fences make good neighbors"

(0, 0).clue: His left arm is buried at Ellwood Farm near Fredericksburg, Virginia
